What I liked the most about Eastern India that we don't indulge in so much of how the culture is portrayed even if certain things don't exactly represent the location or city. The dance forms used in this song are not what typically Bengali culture is known for. The the most famous dance form is Kathak apart from other folk dances and natya. However, if this was somehow done by Hindi cinema or any cinema other than southern cinema while they are representing southern part of India most of the southern part people would have boycotted and objected stating this is not our culture, this is against our sentiments(that's what happened to many movies including meenakshi sundareshwar, (received hate comments from Tamil people in the name of culture even though it actually represented so well as the director Musician all were the representative of their states). I can understand how much of hard work goes into making a movie. Being a Bengali, I really loved the movie. And being from Eastern part of India really don't care if the dance form is what actually we have or is a representation of some other part of the country. I hope this gesture where people who are not from southern states assimilate and accept and don't go into false pride and false nationalism is taken by southern states people as well, a sense of that understanding. We enjoy Bharatnatyam, Kuchipudi as much as Kathak. A very beautiful movie and doesn't matter if they didn't take anyone from Bengali cinema to represent Bengal social movement(what is often argued by most of the people of the southern states). A Wonderful try!

Choreographer has done a brilliant job of fusing different dance forms. Hats off to Anurag and Mickey for this divine composition. Great work by the director as well. Kudos to the whole team. You guys deserve a standing ovation.

I am a Bengali, born and brought up in Kolkata, and I must say right from my childhood I got introduced to South Indian music and art. I am a music aficionado and just like everyone knows Bengal for its art and culture, Bengali's look upto South India and celebrates its music and art forms like no one else. This song has become one of my personal favourite and the core reason being Sai Pallavi. I adore and respect her a lot. When she comes on screen everything around her just freezes, and in this song she is looking absolute divine, feels like true goddess is dancing. She has again proved that dancing is just not about perfect steps it's a lot more than that. Singing, Music, choreography, set everything is stunning and spectacular, and also special mention to Nani, his eyes speaks thousand words. This song in its entirety is a masterpiece. As a Bengali I feel so proud when someone hails our culture and portrays it so beautifully
